Del Monte Pacific (SGX:D03  PSE:DELM) booked a higher net profit attributable to owners of $20.0 million in the fiscal fourth quarter ended April 30  compared with $14.5 million a year ago.Earnings per share went up to $0.0082 from $0.0049 in the year-ago period  according to a Thursday bourse disclosure.Sales for the period increased 14% year over year to $569.5 million from $497.8 million  mainly due to higher sales in the US and higher exports of S&W branded fresh pineapples.The company also approved a final dividend of $0.017 per share for the 12 months ended April 30  an increase of 42% from the prior year's dividend.
